[[File:GDL LOGO COLOR.jpg|thumb|Official logo of GDL Technology]] '''Gesture Description Language''' (GDL or GDL Technology) is a method of describing and automatic (computer) [[Syntactic pattern recognition|syntactic classification]] of gestures and movements created<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Hachaj | first1 = Tomasz | last2 = Ogiela | first2 = Marek R. | year = 2014 | title = Rule-based approach to recognizing human body poses and gestures in real time | url = https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007%2Fs00530-013-0332-2 | journal = Multimedia Systems | volume = 20 | issue = 1| pages = 81–99 | doi=10.1007/s00530-013-0332-2}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Hachaj | first1 = Tomasz | last2 = Ogiela | first2 = Marek R. | year = 2012 | title = Semantic Description and Recognition of Human Body Poses and Movement Sequences with Gesture Description Language, Computer Applications for Bio-technology, Multimedia, and Ubiquitous City | url = https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007%2F978-3-642-35521-9_1 | journal = Communications in Computer and Information Science | volume = 353 | issue = | pages = 1–8 | doi=10.1007/978-3-642-35521-9_1}}</ref> by doctor Tomasz Hachaj<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cci.up.krakow.pl/|title=Cryptography and Cognitive Informatics Research Group, Pedagogical University, Krakow, Poland|website=www.cci.up.krakow.pl}}</ref> (PhD) and professor Marek R. Ogiela<ref>{{cite web|url=http://home.agh.edu.pl/~mogiela/|title=Prof. Dr. Marek R. Ogiela - personal webpage|website=home.agh.edu.pl}}</ref>(PhD, DSc). GDL uses [[Context-free grammar|context-free formal grammar]] named GDLs (Gesture Description Language script). With GDLs it is possible to define rules that describe set of gestures. Those rules play similar role as rules in classic [[expert system]]s. With rules it is possible to define static body positions (so called key frames) and sequences of key frames that create together definitions of gestures or movements. The recognition is done by [[forward chaining]] [[inference engine]]. The latest GDL implementations<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cci.up.krakow.pl/gdl/|title=Gesture Description Language|website=www.cci.up.krakow.pl}}</ref> utilize [[Microsoft]] [[Kinect]] controller and enable real time classification. The license for GDL-based software allows using those programs for educational and scientific purposes for free.
