{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2018}} {{Infobox politician |name=Lina Hidalgo |office=[[County Judge]]-Elect of [[Harris County, Texas]] |term_start=January 2019 |term_end= |succeeding=[[Ed Emmett]] |party =[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1991|2|19}} |birth_place = [[Colombia]] |alma_mater = [[Stanford University]] |residence = [[Houston]], [[Texas]] |occupation = |website = }} '''Lina Maria Hidalgo''' is an American politician from the [[U.S. state|state]] of [[Texas]]. She is the incoming [[county judge]] for [[Harris County, Texas]].
Hidalgo was born in [[Colombia]] on February 19, 1991.<ref name=surprise>{{cite web|last=Despart |first=Zach |url=https://www.chron.com/politics/election/local/article/Hidalgo-surprise-victor-in-Harris-County-judge-13372415.php |title=Hidalgo, surprise victor in Harris County judge race, prepares to lead - Houston Chronicle |publisher=Chron.com |date=November 7, 2018 |accessdate=November 12, 2018}}</ref> She was raised in [[Mexico]] and [[Peru]], before she immigrated to [[Houston]] in 2005.<ref name=surprise/><ref name=abc/> She earned her [[bachelor's degree]] in [[political science]] from [[Stanford University]] in 2013,<ref name=surprise/> and was enrolled in a joint degree program earning a [[master's degree]] from the [[Harvard Kennedy School]] and a [[Juris Doctor]] from the [[New York University School of Law]] when she decided to move back to Houston to run for political office in the [[Texas elections, 2018|2018 elections]].<ref name=surprise/> She took a job as a [[medical interpreter]] at the [[Texas Medical Center]].<ref name=abc>{{cite web|url=https://abc13.com/politics/who-is-newly-elected-harris-county-judge-lina-hidalgo/4637353/|title=Who is newly-elected Harris County Judge Lina Hidalgo?|date=November 7, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=November 12, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Gill |first=Julian |url=https://www.chron.com/news/houston-texas/houston/slideshow/Things-to-know-about-newly-elected-Harris-County-187066.php |title=Things to know about newly elected Harris County Judge Lina Hidalgo - Houston Chronicle |publisher=Chron.com |date=November 7, 2018 |accessdate=November 12, 2018}}</ref>
Hidalgo ran for county judge of Harris County in the 2018 elections, at age 27. She defeated [[incumbent]] [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] [[Ed Emmett]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Lewis |first=Brooke A. |url=https://www.houstonchronicle.com/news/columnists/grieder/article/Lina-Hidalgo-earned-the-right-to-serve-as-Harris-13379553.php |title=Lina Hidalgo earned the right to serve as Harris County judge |publisher=HoustonChronicle.com |date=November 6, 2018 |accessdate=November 12, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/08/us/politics/lina-hidalgo-harris-county.html |title=Lina Hidalgo, a 27-Year-Old Latina, Will Lead Harris County, Texas’ Biggest - The New York Times |publisher=Nytimes.com |date= |accessdate=November 12, 2018}}</ref>
