'''Rajeshwar Shastri Dravid''' (b. 1899–d.-) was an Indian writer, scholar, grammarian and translator of [[Sanskrit literature]].<ref name="Dravid, Rajeshwar Shastri, 1899- ">{{Cite web |url=https://openlibrary.org/subjects/dravid_rajeshwar_shastri_1899- |title=Dravid, Rajeshwar Shastri, 1899-  |last=OpenLibrary.org |date=2018-05-23 |website=openlibrary.org |language=en |access-date=2018-05-23}}</ref> Born in 1899 in the Indian state of [[Uttar Pradesh]], he was the author several books in Sanskrit language]] which included ''Sāṅkhyakārikā'',<ref>{{Cite book |url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/sankhyakarika/oclc/21026070 |title=Sāṅkhyakārikā |last=Īśvarakr̥ṣṇa |last2=Śastrī |first2=Ḍhuṇḍhirāja |last3=Nārāyaṇatīrtha |date=1977 |publisher=Caukhambā Saṃskr̥ta Sīrija Āphisa |location=Vārāṇasī |oclc=21026070}}</ref> ''Bhāratīya-rājanīti-prakaśah''<ref>{{Cite book |url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/bharatiya-rajaniti-prakasah/oclc/23578223 |title=Bhāratīya-rājanīti-prakaśah |last=Drāviḍa |first=Rājeśvara Śāstrī |publisher=Śāradā-gaurava-granthamālā |location=Puṇyapattanam |oclc=23578223}}</ref> and ''R̥ṣikalpanyāsaḥ''.<ref>{{Cite book |url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/rsikalpanyasah/oclc/17814397 |title=R̥ṣikalpanyāsaḥ. |last=Drāviḍa |first=Rājeśvara Śāstrī |last2=Śāstrī |first2=Devadatta |date=1971 |publisher=Bhāratī Pariṣad |location=Prayāga |oclc=17814397}}</ref> His brother, Raja Ram Dravid, was the author of ''The Problem of Universals in Indian Philosophy'', a critique of [[ancient Indian philosophy]].<ref name="Dravid2000">{{cite book|author=Raja Ram Dravid|title=The Problem of Universals in Indian Philosophy|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=59TG5UTBFbgC&pg=PR6|date=31 December 2000|publisher=Motilal Banarsidass Publishe|isbn=978-81-208-0832-4|pages=6–}}</ref> The [[Government of India]] awarded him [[Padma Bhushan]], the third highest Indian civilian award, in 1960.<ref name="Padma Awards">{{Cite web |url=http://www.dashboard-padmaawards.gov.in/ |title=Padma Awards |date=2018-05-17 |website=Padma Awards |publisher=Government of India |access-date=2018-05-17}}</ref>

